Node MUST be installed

/****************************************************/
To install package.json dependencies:

npm install
sudo apt-get install libcairo2-dev libjpeg-dev libpango1.0-dev libgif-dev build-essential g++
/****************************************************/


/****************************************************/
To run the server: nodemon
Nodemon will automatically restart the server when ANY change in the code is made.
/****************************************************/

/****************************************************/
You should read this:
https://github.com/sequelize/express-example
https://github.com/waiyaki/postgres-express-node-tutorial
/****************************************************/


/****************************************************/
To commit without message:
git commit -a --allow-empty-message -m ''
/****************************************************/


Professionals levels:
1 - ADMIN
2 - Medico
=======
/****************************************************/
To create a new sql user:
mysql -u root -p
CREATE USER 'raphael'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY '123';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON * . * TO 'raphael'@'localhost';
/****************************************************/

/****************************************************/
To execute sql script
mysql -u USER -p < script.sql (open terminal in the same path)
/****************************************************/

/****************************************************/
Install order
apt-get install mysql-server
apt-get install mysql-client
apt-get install nodejs
apt-get install npm

create mysqluser
create mysqldb
npm install
npm install -g nodemon
sudo ln -s /usr/bin/nodejs /usr/bin/node
npm install passport
nodemon
/****************************************************/
PATH TO MERGE TO MASTER:
check if you are in your branch
git branch
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git push origin <your_branch>
git pull origin master
    correct conflicts if any
        git push origin <your_branch>

git push origin <your_branch>
git checkout master
git pull origin master
    (if your branch is behind any commits)
        git add .
git merge <your_branch>
git push origin master

TROCAR SENHA MYSQL:

ALTER USER 'user'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'new_password';
